public enum AttributeHandlingType extends Enum<AttributeHandlingType>
The AttributeHandlingType enum contains the list of all of the different ways that attributes can be aggregated. Note that there is no explicit mapping from attribute type to allowable attribute aggregation type. That mapping is contained within the various AttributeHandlingType arrays defined below.

Cytoscape Backwards Compatibility (Enum): This class is an enum therefore can't be extended by users. This means that we may add methods or enum values for minor version updates. Methods or enum values will only be removed for major version updates.
